parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Takata airbag inflator can cause the airbag to rupture, resulting in metal fragments striking the driver or other vehicle occupants, leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: None reported
as the issue is related to a potential future failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of available parts for the Takata airbag recall repair can leave vehicles unrepaired, putting drivers and passengers at risk of serious injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Delayed or unavailable repair parts
inability to schedule repair appointments
lack of communication from dealerships or manufacturers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Poor communication from manufacturers and dealerships can lead to frustration, inconvenience, and a lack of trust among vehicle owners, potentially delaying necessary repairs and putting drivers and passengers at risk.
symptoms: Unreturned phone calls
unresponsive dealerships
lack of information about repair status
conflicting information from manufacturers and dealerships.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of an accident can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Airbags did not deploy in a crash
vehicle damage
potential injury or death.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Engine Stalling and Loss of Power Steering
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent engine stalling can cause loss of power steering, leading to a loss of vehicle control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when slowing down or cornering.
symptoms: The engine shuts down completely when slowing down
cornering

or sitting at red lights; loss of power steering; abnormal knocking sound from the engine; engine shakes and jerks as if it wants to turn off; hesitation or stalling when accelerating or decelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal to return to its normal position can cause the vehicle to fail to stop, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle fails to come to a complete stop
the emergency brake does not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The grinding noise while braking can indicate a faulty brake system, which can lead to reduced stopping power and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Loud grinding noise while depressing the brake pedal
spring missing on the parking brake.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Whining, Ticking, and Clicking Noises in Rotor/Brake
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unusual noises in the rotor/brake can indicate a faulty brake system, which can lead to reduced stopping power and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Whining noise in the back
ticking and clicking noise in the rotor/brake
rough drive
and seat sagging.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The occasional brake failure can cause the vehicle to fail to stop, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Brakes work fine
then go nearly to the floor when they fail
engine speed increases slightly
AWD system may interfere with brake function.
